1. OVERVIEW
-----------

afterdark-darkd supports five types of plugins:

- Service:    Add new monitoring/security services to the daemon
- DataSource: Provide threat intel feeds, API integrations
- Storage:    Alternative storage backends (databases, cloud)
- Reporter:   Generate reports in various formats (PDF, HTML, CSV)
- CLI:        Add commands to the admin and user CLIs

Plugins are standalone executables that communicate with the daemon via
gRPC over local sockets. This architecture provides:

- Process isolation (plugin crashes don't affect the daemon)
- Language independence (plugins can be written in any gRPC language)
- Version independence (plugins can be updated without daemon restart)
- Security (plugins run with their own privileges)


2. PLUGIN TYPES
---------------

Service Plugin:
  - Adds monitoring/security capabilities
  - Has full lifecycle (Start, Stop, Health, Execute)
  - Can perform periodic tasks
  - Example: custom vulnerability scanner

DataSource Plugin:
  - Provides external data feeds
  - Supports query and subscription patterns
  - Example: threat intelligence feed

Storage Plugin:
  - Provides alternative storage backends
  - Key-value and query interfaces
  - Example: Redis, PostgreSQL, S3

Reporter Plugin:
  - Generates reports from security data
  - Multiple output formats
  - Example: PDF compliance report generator

CLI Plugin:
  - Adds commands to darkdadm and darkapi CLIs
  - Full argument and flag support
  - Example: custom reporting commands


3. QUICK START
--------------

Import the plugin SDK:

    import sdk "github.com/afterdarksys/afterdark-darkd/pkg/pluginsdk"

Create a service plugin:

    package main

    import (
        "context"
        sdk "github.com/afterdarksys/afterdark-darkd/pkg/pluginsdk"
    )

    type MyPlugin struct {
        sdk.BaseServicePlugin
    }

    func (p *MyPlugin) Info() sdk.PluginInfo {
        return sdk.PluginInfo{
            Name:        "my-plugin",
            Version:     "1.0.0",
            Type:        sdk.PluginTypeService,
            Description: "My custom plugin",
            Author:      "Your Name",
        }
    }

    func (p *MyPlugin) Execute(ctx context.Context, action string,
        params map[string]interface{}) (map[string]interface{}, error) {
        // Your implementation
        return nil, nil
    }

    func main() {
        sdk.ServeServicePlugin(&MyPlugin{})
    }

Build and install:

    go build -o my-plugin .
    sudo cp my-plugin /var/lib/afterdark-darkd/plugins/
    sudo chmod +x /var/lib/afterdark-darkd/plugins/my-plugin


4. SERVICE PLUGIN GUIDE
-----------------------

The ServicePlugin interface:

    type ServicePlugin interface {
        Info() PluginInfo
        Configure(config map[string]interface{}) error
        Start(ctx context.Context) error
        Stop(ctx context.Context) error
        Health() PluginHealth
        Execute(ctx context.Context, action string,
            params map[string]interface{}) (map[string]interface{}, error)
    }

Use BaseServicePlugin for default implementations:

    type MyService struct {
        sdk.BaseServicePlugin
        // Your fields here
    }

The BaseServicePlugin provides:
- Configure(): Stores config, accessible via Config()
- Start()/Stop(): State management
- Health(): Basic health reporting
- SetState(): Update plugin state and message

Override methods as needed:

    func (s *MyService) Start(ctx context.Context) error {
        // Call base implementation
        if err := s.BaseServicePlugin.Start(ctx); err != nil {
            return err
        }
        // Your startup logic
        go s.runBackgroundTask()
        return nil
    }

    func (s *MyService) Execute(ctx context.Context, action string,
        params map[string]interface{}) (map[string]interface{}, error) {
        switch action {
        case "scan":
            return s.performScan(params)
        case "status":
            return s.getStatus()
        default:
            return nil, fmt.Errorf("unknown action: %s", action)
        }
    }

See examples/plugins/hello-service/ for a complete example.


5. DATA SOURCE PLUGIN GUIDE
---------------------------

The DataSourcePlugin interface:

    type DataSourcePlugin interface {
        Info() PluginInfo
        Configure(config map[string]interface{}) error
        Connect(ctx context.Context) error
        Disconnect(ctx context.Context) error
        Query(ctx context.Context, query string,
            params map[string]interface{}) ([]map[string]interface{}, error)
        Subscribe(ctx context.Context, topic string,
            handler func(data map[string]interface{})) error
        Health() PluginHealth
    }

Example threat intel feed:

    type ThreatFeed struct {
        sdk.BaseDataSourcePlugin
        client *http.Client
    }

    func (f *ThreatFeed) Connect(ctx context.Context) error {
        f.client = &http.Client{Timeout: 30 * time.Second}
        f.SetState(sdk.PluginStateRunning, "connected")
        return nil
    }

    func (f *ThreatFeed) Query(ctx context.Context, query string,
        params map[string]interface{}) ([]map[string]interface{}, error) {
        // Fetch and return threat indicators
        return f.fetchIndicators(query, params)
    }

See examples/plugins/threatfeed-datasource/ for a complete example.


6. STORAGE PLUGIN GUIDE
-----------------------

The StoragePlugin interface:

    type StoragePlugin interface {
        Info() PluginInfo
        Configure(config map[string]interface{}) error
        Connect(ctx context.Context) error
        Disconnect(ctx context.Context) error
        Get(ctx context.Context, collection, key string) ([]byte, error)
        Set(ctx context.Context, collection, key string, value []byte) error
        Delete(ctx context.Context, collection, key string) error
        List(ctx context.Context, collection, prefix string) ([]string, error)
        Query(ctx context.Context, collection string,
            query map[string]interface{}) ([][]byte, error)
        Health() PluginHealth
    }

Example Redis storage:

    type RedisStorage struct {
        sdk.BaseStoragePlugin
        client *redis.Client
    }

    func (s *RedisStorage) Get(ctx context.Context,
        collection, key string) ([]byte, error) {
        fullKey := collection + ":" + key
        return s.client.Get(ctx, fullKey).Bytes()
    }


7. REPORTER PLUGIN GUIDE
------------------------

The ReporterPlugin interface:

    type ReporterPlugin interface {
        Info() PluginInfo
        Configure(config map[string]interface{}) error
        SupportedFormats() []string
        Generate(ctx context.Context, format string,
            data map[string]interface{}) ([]byte, error)
        Health() PluginHealth
    }

Example PDF reporter:

    type PDFReporter struct {
        sdk.BaseReporterPlugin
    }

    func (r *PDFReporter) SupportedFormats() []string {
        return []string{"pdf", "html"}
    }

    func (r *PDFReporter) Generate(ctx context.Context, format string,
        data map[string]interface{}) ([]byte, error) {
        switch format {
        case "pdf":
            return r.generatePDF(data)
        case "html":
            return r.generateHTML(data)
        }
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("unsupported format: %s", format)
    }


8. CLI PLUGIN GUIDE
-------------------

The CLIPlugin interface:

    type CLIPlugin interface {
        Info() PluginInfo
        Configure(config map[string]interface{}) error
        Commands() []CLICommand
        Execute(ctx context.Context, command string, args []string,
            flags map[string]interface{}) (string, error)
        Health() PluginHealth
    }

Define commands:

    func (p *MyCLI) Commands() []sdk.CLICommand {
        return []sdk.CLICommand{
            {
                Name:        "scan",
                Description: "Run a security scan",
                Usage:       "scan [target]",
                Flags: []sdk.CLIFlag{
                    {
                        Name:        "output",
                        Shorthand:   "o",
                        Description: "Output format",
                        Type:        "string",
                        Default:     "json",
                    },
                    {
                        Name:        "verbose",
                        Shorthand:   "v",
                        Description: "Verbose output",
                        Type:        "bool",
                    },
                },
            },
        }
    }

Handle execution:

    func (p *MyCLI) Execute(ctx context.Context, command string,
        args []string, flags map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {
        switch command {
        case "scan":
            target := ""
            if len(args) > 0 {
                target = args[0]
            }
            format := flags["output"].(string)
            return p.runScan(target, format)
        }
        return "", fmt.Errorf("unknown command: %s", command)
    }


9. BUILDING AND INSTALLING
--------------------------

Build your plugin:

    go build -o my-plugin .

Install to plugin directory:

    sudo mkdir -p /var/lib/afterdark-darkd/plugins
    sudo cp my-plugin /var/lib/afterdark-darkd/plugins/
    sudo chmod +x /var/lib/afterdark-darkd/plugins/my-plugin

Cross-compile for other platforms:

    # Linux
    GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o my-plugin-linux-amd64 .

    # Windows
    GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o my-plugin-windows-amd64.exe .

    # macOS ARM
    GOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o my-plugin-darwin-arm64 .


10. CONFIGURATION
-----------------

Plugins receive configuration via the Configure() method. Configuration
is passed as a map[string]interface{}.

In darkd.yaml, configure plugins:

    daemon:
      plugin_dir: /var/lib/afterdark-darkd/plugins

    plugins:
      my-plugin:
        api_key: "secret123"
        endpoint: "https://api.example.com"
        timeout_seconds: 30

Access in your plugin:

    func (p *MyPlugin) Configure(config map[string]interface{}) error {
        if err := p.BaseServicePlugin.Configure(config); err != nil {
            return err
        }

        if key, ok := config["api_key"].(string); ok {
            p.apiKey = key
        }

        if timeout, ok := config["timeout_seconds"].(float64); ok {
            p.timeout = time.Duration(timeout) * time.Second
        }

        return nil
    }


11. DEBUGGING
-------------

Enable debug logging:

    export PLUGIN_LOG_LEVEL=debug

Use the SDK logger:

    logger := sdk.Logger("my-plugin")
    logger.Info("plugin started", "version", "1.0.0")
    logger.Debug("processing request", "action", action)

Test your plugin standalone:

    # Run plugin directly (it will wait for daemon connection)
    ./my-plugin

    # Check if plugin is properly detected
    afterdark-darkd status --plugins

Common issues:

1. Plugin not loading:
   - Check file permissions (must be executable)
   - Check plugin directory path
   - Check daemon logs for errors

2. gRPC connection failed:
   - Ensure plugin is compiled for correct OS/arch
   - Check for port conflicts

3. Configuration not received:
   - Verify YAML syntax in darkd.yaml
   - Check plugin name matches config section


